## Dual compliance gates

Release-quality changes for this generator must pass **both** compliance gates:

| Gate | Role | Scope |
|------|------|-------|
| **A — OAS composition fixtures** | Spec correctness | ~15 named fixture schemas exercising every lowering rule (no OpenAI dependency) |
| **B — OpenAI corpus** | Scale and realism | Full generate → compile → type inventory → golden round-trips against the pinned OpenAI document (~891 anyOf, ~254 oneOf, ~832 nullable branches) |

Release is blocked while either gate has non-deferred `FAIL`s.

**Gate A** is OAS-only — no dependency on OpenAI type names, vendor extensions,
or patterns. A Gate A failure always indicates a spec-level codegen defect.

**Gate B** validates that the general lowering rules work at scale on a real-world
document. It runs the full pipeline: generate client code, C++ compile the library,
inventory every composed schema's C++ type against expected types, and run golden
round-trip tests that verify encode/decode fidelity for representative schemas.
Non-deferred FAIL in any Gate B step blocks release.

> **Maintainer note:** Both gates live in the `openai-cpp-sdk/` directory of the
> OpenAPI Generator monorepo. See the `oas-compliance/README.md` and
> `openai/compliance/MANIFEST.md` for gate-specific documentation and run commands.

