## CI policy

The dual compliance gates are **not yet wired into CI**.  Until CI integration is
complete, a maintainer must run the gates manually before tagging any release that
includes changes to `cpp-boost-beast-client`:

```sh
# From the monorepo root:
./openai-cpp-sdk/run-dual-gates.sh
```

Both gates must exit 0 with no non-deferred FAILs before the release proceeds.
CI integration (parallel Gate A / Gate B execution on Beast-generator changes) is
tracked as a separate work item.

